<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,258,427]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Described from 
<collectingCountry box="[333,404,258,282]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, this thrips has been recorded widely in Central 
<collectingCountry box="[942,1038,258,282]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">America</collectingCountry>
on several plant species (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Marullo R. (1996) The Thrips of Central and South America: An Introduction. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 6, 1 - 488." type="journal article" year="1996">
Mound &amp; Marullo 
<number box="[252,312,294,318]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Because of its unusual eyes, with two ventral and three anterolateral ommatidia enlarged, this species was placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[409,624,331,355]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Exophthalmothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,624,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Exophthalmothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Retana-Salazar" box="[671,929,330,354]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Retana-Salazar, A. P. (1998) Reestablecimiento de los generos Frankliniella, Exophthalmothrips y Bolbothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Revista de Biologia Tropical, 46 (2), 385 - 396." type="journal article" year="1998">
Retana-Salazar (
<number box="[859,920,330,354]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. That author stated that the posteromarginal comb on tergite VIII is incomplete medially, but on the 
<typeStatus box="[795,893,366,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
the comb is complete and with relatively short teeth. The fore wings and antennal segments are largely brown, except for the paler antennal segment III.
</paragraph>
